did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.unittitle: Frederick Morrison Babcock publications, 1941-1973
did.physdesc: Publications, including land valuations, estimates, reports and development studies.
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract:
Publications, including land valuations, estimates, reports and development studies by Frederick Morrison Babcock. Areas represented in these studies are located in Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Maryland, Minnesota, Missouri, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, Nevada, New Mexico, Pennsylvania, Virginia and Washington,
D.C.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Frederick Morrison Babcock (1898-1983) and his brother Henry Babcock were affiliated with their father's real estate appraisal firm, William H. Babcock and Sons.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Publications, including land valuations, estimates, reports and development studies by Frederick Morrison Babcock. Areas represented in these studies are located in Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Maryland, Minnesota, Missouri, New Jersey, New York, North Carolina, Nevada, New Mexico, Pennsylvania, Virginia and Washington, D.C.

prefercite.head: Cite As:
prefercite.p: Frederick Morrison Babcock Publications, #4087. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.

relatedmaterial.head: RELATED MATERIAL
relatedmaterial.p: Related collection: William H. Babcock and Sons. Records. University of Wyoming, Archive of Contemporary History.
